'''
Solution for question 6 of Rosalind Bioinformatics stronghold
Title: Counting Point Mutations
'''
#Given DNA strings are named as "s" and "t"
s=""
t=""
#The Hamming distance between two strings is simply the number of positions in the strings at which corresponding symbols differ.
'''
Expected Output:
The number of positions in the strings at which corresponding symbols differ.
'''
count=0
for x,y in zip(s,t):
    if x!=y:
      count+=1
print(count)
#Output: 493